The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Former India captain Sourav Ganguly has apologised for failing to attend the launch of the book Shadows Across the Playing Field, by Shashi Tharoor and Shaharyar Khan, at a city hotel on Saturday evening. Apart from the Union minister, Governor Gopalkrishna Gandhi attended the event, for which Sourav was late. Souravs text message, Sorry for this delay. Hope it went well. My loss. Sincere apol (apologies), had reached the organisers within half an hour of the programme ending, via one of the guests. Priya Kapoor, a director with the publisher, Roli Books, said: He told us that he was extremely sorry that he could not make it on time.    A tobacco container, lying on a wall of SSKM Hospital, triggered a bomb scare on Sunday morning. Police said relatives of patients spotted the container, which had wires hanging out, near the emergency department around 7.30am and informed the authorities. A bomb detection and disposal squad team with sniffer dogs rushed to the spot. Cops found two bulb holders in the container.    Shashanka Sekhar Kundu, a taxi driver, on Sunday returned a laptop and Rs 9,000 that a passenger had left in his taxi on Saturday evening.    A Tata Indica (WB-02U-3462) was stolen from New Alipores Block B early on Sunday.                                                                                                                                                                   
